# Core Package

## Purpose

`@dukkani/core` is the central initialization layer for server-side auth and database access.
It composes `@dukkani/auth`, `@dukkani/db`, and `@dukkani/env` into safe singleton entrypoints.

## Public API

- `getDatabase()` and `database`
- `getAuth()` and `auth`

## Responsibilities

- Initialize database and auth lazily and only once.
- Enforce preview-environment safeguards before DB initialization.
- Keep dependency order explicit (`database` before `auth`).

## Constraints

- Do not import from any `apps/*` code.
- Keep this package environment-aware through `@dukkani/env` presets.
- Avoid business-domain logic here; this package is composition and bootstrapping only.

## Best Practices

- Prefer importing `database`/`auth` from `@dukkani/core` in server-side code that needs fully wired instances.
- Keep initialization side effects deterministic and idempotent.
- Any new singleton must follow the same lazy initialization pattern.
